<section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-6 px-4 py-12">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
    Frequently <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">Asked</span> Questions
  </h1>
  <dl class="space-y-4">
    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">What is <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">TecHub</span>?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        TecHub is a GitHub‑native profile and content layer — a tasteful “TechDeck for GitHub.” It turns your public GitHub activity into a rich, shareable profile with optional AI‑assisted artwork and summaries.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">How does it <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">work</span>?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 space-y-2">
        <p><span class="font-semibold">Two modes:</span> Use repo‑based config (“GitHub mode”) or manage via UI (“Managed mode”). You can switch without losing data.</p>
        <p><span class="font-semibold">JSON‑first:</span> Everything shown on profiles is available at <code class="whitespace-nowrap">/profiles/:username.json</code> for dashboards and embeds.</p>
        <p><span class="font-semibold">Optional AI:</span> Artwork and summaries are opt‑in, quota‑bounded, and always overrideable by you.</p>
        <p><span class="font-semibold">Open source:</span> Minimal scopes, transparent ops, and auditable code.</p>
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Why an <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">eligibility gate</span> instead of a fee?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Keeping TecHub free means we vet profiles for meaningful public signal (account age, active repos,
        social proof, recent activity). Hitting at least three signals passes. If you miss, we’ll surface why
        and you can try again after levelling up.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Why the <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">GitHub App</span> install?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        App‑level credentials unlock higher rate limits and faster background syncs. We scope permissions tightly
        and rotate tokens via Solid Queue.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Do you store my GitHub <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">token</span>?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Access tokens are encrypted at rest (Active Record Encryption). They only authorise TecHub features on your
        behalf and can be revoked anytime in your GitHub settings.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Where does the <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">information</span> come from?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        TecHub uses the GitHub API to analyse public data — profile fields, repos, topics, languages, and activity —
        plus an optional URL you can submit for extra context. We never access private repositories or secrets.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Is this just <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">OSINT</span>?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        It’s open‑source intelligence in service of builders. TecHub organises what you’ve already made public and turns
        it into a focused, celebratory snapshot — not an attempt to uncover private information.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">Can I stay <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">anonymous</span> or pseudonymous?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Yes. If your GitHub identity is pseudonymous, your card will reflect that. We only use public data associated
        with your GitHub handle.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">What if I never signed up but see my <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">profile</span>?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Cards can be created based on public GitHub activity or seeded by the team. You can claim your card to refresh it
        or request removal if you prefer not to be included.
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">How do I <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 via-cyan-600 to-emerald-600 bg-clip-text text-transparent dark:from-blue-400 dark:via-cyan-400 dark:to-emerald-400 animate-gradient">claim</span> or remove a profile?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
