        <p><span class="font-semibold">Overrides:</span> You can hide or remove any self‑identifying info from your profile, and you can set a separate contact email at Settings → Account (it does not have to be your GitHub email).</p>
      </dd>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-4 dark:border-slate-700 dark:bg-slate-900/70">
      <dt class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">I see an “Available for hire” badge — can I turn it off here?</dt>
      <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">
        Yes. Go to <span class="font-semibold">My Profiles → Settings → Privacy & Sharing</span> and toggle “Show the ‘Available for hire’ badge.”
        This only affects your TecHub profile display and does not change your GitHub setting.
      </dd>
    </div>

  </dl>
